snippet.textDisplay:
The WHO said on January 23 that the outbreak did not constitute a public emergency of international concern and there was "no evidence" of the virus spreading between humans outside of China.

On January 30, the WHO declared coronavirus a global emergency as the death toll in China jumped to 170, with 7,711 cases reported in the country, where the virus had spread to all 31 provinces.

The Trump administration restricted travel from China on Jan. 31 in response to the mounting coronavirus threat -- a move many Democrats and media outlets characterized as irresponsible and unnecessary.

from Japan.
Please use the mask by following the President of the United States. I would like to talk a bit about how few Japanese people are infected worldwide.
Approximately 2,000 infected people in Japan. Half of them are non-Japanese nationals. Most Japanese people wear masks.
In comparison, non-Japanese people don't wear masks much. As a result, the number of infected people increases despite the demographically low number of non-Japanese citizens.
The virus measures taken by Japanese are as follows.
1, mask when going out.
2, hand washing.
3, gargle.
4, face washing.
About this. This works well. In the case of Japan, it was originally a countermeasure against influenza, not a coronavirus. However, this influenza control was effective against coronavirus.
Influenza is a similar virus to coronavirus. For this reason, the number of infected people in Japan is not as large as in other countries.
Last but not least, I will put statistics on the number of people infected with influenza in Japan. I think it is enough evidence. Please go to the four daily.

snippet.textDisplay: I don't pretend to be an expert, but I am 76 years old and so I've either had experiences or heard of things at one time or another, regarding car accidents. The bulk of them are caused by one or more factors, DUI (alcohol, illegal drugs or a medical prescription),  distracted driving whether electronic toys or unruly children, fatigue or sleepiness,  the elderly in age-denial, and lastly and importantly, road rage  But a significant fraction of these car accidents are medically related. The other grandfather in my family had a car accident in his own garage. He drove into it, but failed to stop, because he was stricken with a brain aneurysm and had lost consciousness.  Another man committed multiple hit-and-ran incidents before also losing consciousness, he was in insulin shock. And now today on April 1, 2020, this video is telling me of car accident victims who were also positive with COVID-19.  Yes, I believe it. To me, it is credible.
